sentences: Mai Endo (遠藤 舞, Endō Mai, born July 31, 1988) is a Japanese idol, singer and talent from Tokyo.
She made her solo debut as a singer on July 13, 2013.
Two weeks before being scouted for the Idoling!!!
In November 2006, she passed the Idoling!!!
In March 2009, when the former leader, Sayaka Katō, graduated, she became the next leader of the group.
In May 2011, she starred in, and sang the theme song for an independent film Koneko no Kimochi (コネコノキモチ).
After being in the group for 7.5 years, she graduated from Idoling!!!
on February 14, 2014, at Zepp DiverCity in Odaiba, Tokyo to focus on her solo career.
